alert.note: Alert for Grays Harbor; King; Kitsap; Lewis; Mason; Pierce; Thurston (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Advisory issued October 25 at 4:46PM PDT by NWS Seattle
info.description: .A heavy band of precipitation is moving into the area and will impact the I-5 corridor over the next several hours. ...FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 845 PM PDT THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Urban and small stream flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected. * WHERE...Portions of northwest Washington and west central Washington, including the following counties, in northwest Washington, Grays Harbor, Kitsap and Mason. In west central Washington, King, Lewis, Pierce and Thurston. * WHEN...Until 845 PM PDT. * IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas. Ponding of water in urban or other areas is occurring or is imminent. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 443 PM PDT, Doppler radar indicated a heavy band of precipitation is moving into the area and will impact the I-5 corridor over the next several hours. This will cause urban and small stream flooding. Overflowing poor drainage areas will cause minor flooding in the advisory area. Between 0.3 and 0.6 inches of rain have fallen. - Additional rainfall amounts of 0.1 to 0.3 inches are expected over the area. This additional rain will result in minor flooding. - Some locations that will experience flooding include... Tacoma, Kent, Federal Way, Auburn, Olympia, Bremerton, Puyallup, Centralia, Shelton, Belfair, Toledo, Packwood, Snoqualmie Pass, Lacey, Des Moines, Maple Valley, Covington, Bonney Lake, Tumwater and Enumclaw. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
